      · simp
    · use {![0, 0], ![1, 0], ![0.5, Real.sqrt 3 / 2], ![0.5, -Real.sqrt 3 / 2]}
      constructor
      · rw [hb₀]; intro A hA B hB hAB; simp at * <;> aesop (add simp [dist, EuclideanSpace.norm_def, Real.sqrt_add_square_sq])
      · simp
    · sorry -- Construction for n > 4: use k-pairs and one-triple on a circle as described.
  · ext n
    constructor
    · rintro ⟨hn, s, hbal, hcf, hs⟩
